<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12115e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12115e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12115e"> 115(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> back to 55 y<sup>rs</sup> ago</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">POSTAL RETROGRESSION. Mr. P. Donohue, Chairman, at the meeting of the Kilkenny Farmers&rsquo; Union, stated that an old postman had informed him that the postal services are <mark>back to where they were fifty-five years ago</mark>, both as regards services and charges. It was decided to ask the Government to appoint a commission to inquire into the postal and telegraphic services in rural areas. <small> <a name="IT22aug24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT22aug24"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (22 August 1924) 6/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
